dialog_nodes.title: Not Free Resources for Data Structures

values.text:
Easy to Advanced Data Structures on Udemy is one of the best paid online courses to learn about Data Structures. This course doesn’t expect you to have any prior knowledge of data structures, but a basic prior knowledge of Java is helpful.
Mastering Data Structures & Algorithms using C and C++ on Udemy is one of the best paid online courses to learn about Data Structures. This course is one of the best-sellers on Udemy and received much positive feedback from the students.
LinkedIn Learning has many courses on Data Structures, ranging from easy to advanced. The courses come with exercise files for students to work on while watching the lectures. LinkedIn Learning only costs 30 USD a month and is free for students within certain educational institutions.
Algoexpert.io video series on data structures is the ultimate crash course on this important topic. This program covers fundamental concepts and will help you practice for your coding interviews. It only costs 129 USD per year.

values.text:
According to the U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics, computer science is a multifaceted field, and new graduates with computer science degrees might find a job in a wide variety of industries. In general, the median annual salary for computer and information technology occupations was 82,860 USD as of May 2016.

Also, according to Glassdoor, computer scientist salaries are estimated at 99,050 USD.

Top 8 companies that hire the most computer science majors, according to GeekWire, are below. (Please open in new tab.) -CSC -AppLabs -General Dynamics -Microsoft -Deloitte -Amazon -ManTech International -Raytheon Read more about each company here.

"Employment of computer and information research scientists is projected to grow 16 percent from 2018 to 2028, much faster than the average for all occupations. Computer scientists are likely to enjoy excellent job prospects, because many companies report difficulties finding these highly skilled workers." See 5 Trends in Computer Science Research.

generic.title: Is this what you are looking for?

values.text: According to U.S. News, the following types of jobs are positions where a degree in computer science is a major asset: -Data scientist -Software tester -Web developer -Systems analyst -Business analyst -Product manager -Network architect -Software engineer See more here.

"Depauw University explains the most important aspect of computer science is problem solving. In computer science, students learn about the design, development, and analysis of software and hardware used to solve a variety of problems in different contexts, such as in business, science, and social sciences."

Computer scientists use programming technologies to solve various problems. From building mobile applications to developing software, the main purpose is to assist humans with finishing tasks and solving issues arising in different contexts. For example, computer scientists can create a software program to predict the weather in the next coming week based on some history data.

generic.title: Is this what you are looking for?

values.text: Computer science is a very challenging major. Computer Science Education Week states that "fewer than 3% of college students graduate with computer science and out of all STEM graduates, only 8% of graduates are in computer science." Read more interesting facts about the state of computer science here.
According to Data USA, the number of Computer Sciences and Support Services graduates in the workforce has grown at a rate of 4.78% from 2017 to 2018. Read more here.

generic.title: Is this what you are looking for?

values.text: In 2016, Computer Science climbed to 4th most popular STEM major for college-bound students. In 2013, Computer Science was the 8th most-popular STEM major/career. See more here.

"Computer science is the third most popular major amongst international students coming to the United States. There are many reasons that computer science is so popular, including exceptional job security, uncommonly high starting salaries, and diverse job opportunities across industries." Click here for more.

Is it worth majoring in computer science? One Quora user explains, computer science (CS) is still a good major and is worth learning because it can be useful in jobs requiring programming skills. Read other opinions here.

values.text:
The CS 50 : Introduction to Computer Science course by Harvard University is one of the best free online courses to learn about Data Structures.
Data Structures Concepts & Singly Linked List Implementation is free on Udemy. This course will teach the basic fundamentals of data structures. It will help students and software engineers visualize how different data structures work.
Data Structures Easy to Advanced Course on Youtube can help you learn Data Structures by using step-by-step instructions. This is an 8-hour course from Google engineer William Fisetthat.
You can also earn certifications through freecodecamp.org and display them on your Linkedin profile or resume. Coding Interview Prep by Freecodecamp contains a section on Data Structures. It is good practice for future coding interviews.

Here are some examples of areas in computer science that you can explore:
Artificial Intelligence: Develop computers that simulate human learning and reasoning ability.
Computer Architecture: Design new components and systems for everything from high-performance networked parallel machines to low-cost and low-power iPods.
Computer Design and Engineering: Design new computer circuits, microchips, or other electronic components.
Theoretical Computer Science: Investigate fundamental theories of how computers solve problems and apply the results to other areas of computer science.
Information Technology: Develop and manage information systems that support business or organization.
Operating Systems and Networks: Develop basic software that computers for self-supervision or inter-communication with other computers.
Software Applications: Apply computing and technology for problem solving outside the computer field, for example, education or medicine.
Software Engineering: Develop methods for the production of software systems efficiently and effectively.
